-- Greece's Alpha Bank posts H1 profit, books deferred tax asset  
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 10:31AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, Aug 28 (Reuters) - Alpha Bank <ACBr.AT>, Greece's fourth-largest lender by assets, on Thursday reported a net profit in the first half after booking a deferred tax asset.

Alpha posted a net profit of 267.4 million euros (352 million) after recognising a 422 million euro deferred tax asset in the second quarter. Excluding the one-off tax benefit it lost 165.5 million in the first half, which was in line with market expectations. Analysts polled by Reuters had forecast a loss of 160 million euros on average.